<p><strong>Pleiades gives scholars, students and enthusiasts worldwide the ability to use, create and share historical geographic information about the Greek and Roman World in digital form.</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="places">Get information about ancient places</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.atlantides.org/trac/pleiades/wiki/PleiadesCommunity" target="_self">Join the community to add and modify content</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.atlantides.org/trac/pleiades/" target="_self">Learn more about the project</a></li>
</ul>

<p class="discrete">Pleiades is a joint project of the <a title="AWMC" href="http://www.unc.edu/awmc/">Ancient World Mapping Center</a>, the <a title="Stoa" href="http://www.stoa.org/">Stoa Consortium</a> and the <a title="ISAW" href="http://www.nyu.edu/isaw/">Institute for the Study of the Ancient World</a>. It is supported by its institutional partners, and by the U.S. <a href="http://www.neh.gov/">National Endowment for the Humanities</a>.</p>
